              ### 1. The HTML5 visualisation

              To learn how to use the HTML5 visualisation webapp, check out the [visualisation guide](vizhelp.html).

              ### 2. Generating visualisations from data

              If you want to generate `peptagram` visualisations from standard proteomics data formats, then follow the [installation and visualisation-generation guide](vizgen.html).

              ### 3. Custom visualisation

              If you know python well and want to generate `peptagram` visualisations using custom data, then wade into the [programming api guide](api.html).

              ### 4. Open source contributions

              If you know both python and javascript, you might even want to improve `peptagram` itself. Then fork and pull-request at <http://github.com/boscoh/peptagram>.
